	abstract = {Background and Aims Predicting the response of plant communities to variation in resources and disturbance is still a challenge, because findings depend on how ecological gradients are characterized and how grassland functional composition is assessed. Focusing on leaf dry matter content ({LDMC}), the efficacy of different methods for evaluating the best response of plant communities to either environmental or disturbance change is examined.
