 both ambient and doubled {CO}2, maximum biomass was produced with cuttings of leaf area index {\textgreater}1, and at cutting intervals of 20 and 17 d for ambient and increased {CO}2 environments, respectively. Under high {CO}2 conditions the cutting interval for maximum yield was 15\% shorter than at ambient {CO}2. However, the gain in harvested biomass obtained by reducing the cutting interval by 3 d under high {CO}2 conditions was negligible.},
